Romans chapter 10 gives us maybe the clearest roadmap for evangelism, what it is and how to do it that there is anywhere in the Bible in one spot.

20:08.772 --> 20:10.034
In Romans chapter 10,

20:10.242 --> 20:17.914
God is explaining this thing called evangelism and what the gospel is and how to share it with other people.

20:17.974 --> 20:20.898
He's doing this through the pen of the Apostle Paul.

20:22.260 --> 20:24.904
In Romans chapter 10, here's what the Bible says.

20:26.286 --> 20:27.588
I'm gonna start with verse 13.

20:27.949 --> 20:29.211
Go to verse 15 just for now.

20:31.133 --> 20:35.921
God says for it is by believing in your heart that you were made right with God.

20:37.203 --> 20:39.506
And it is by openly declaring your faith

20:39.906 --> 20:41.047
that you were saved.

20:42.589 --> 20:49.415
So the clear message is not believing in Christ means I'm not right with God.

20:51.097 --> 20:56.262
As the scriptures tell us, anyone who trusts in Him will never be disgraced.

20:56.983 --> 20:59.045
Jew and Gentile are the same in this respect.

20:59.085 --> 21:03.229
They have the same Lord who gives generously to all who call on Him.

21:03.769 --> 21:08.594
For everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.

21:09.954 --> 21:10.855
That's the gospel.

21:11.496 --> 21:14.541
That's the good news of Christ.

21:14.921 --> 21:16.163
Starts out with bad news.

21:16.263 --> 21:22.393
Bad news is because of sin, my relationship with God that I was created for is ruptured.

21:23.234 --> 21:24.335
My sin ruptured it.

21:24.876 --> 21:34.671
Now God loves me unconditionally, period as is, but he's not going to lower his standards of righteousness just to hang out with me.

21:35.772 --> 21:39.538
You see, I can never do enough good stuff to get to God.

21:39.810 --> 21:44.676
you will never do enough good things to get to God.

21:44.696 --> 21:46.618
That's why it takes faith in Christ.

21:47.039 --> 21:53.807
Christ is the only one who could accomplish enough to bring us back into right relationship with God.

21:54.147 --> 22:03.319
If you spent the rest of your life at the intersection of sixth in Congress, helping little old ladies cross the street doing good works, it ain't gonna be enough.

22:03.819 --> 22:06.162
Take your neighbor with a smile on your face, it ain't enough.

22:08.770 --> 22:09.992
He was like, I'm gonna go to heaven.

22:10.012 --> 22:10.873
I'm a good guy.

22:10.893 --> 22:11.834
I'm a good person.

22:13.396 --> 22:14.117
I'm a good guy.

22:14.157 --> 22:14.958
I'm a good girl.

22:15.880 --> 22:17.261
And I'm sure you are.

22:18.203 --> 22:19.464
I try to be a good guy.

22:19.484 --> 22:22.989
I'm not good enough to get to God.

22:24.191 --> 22:26.654
He is morally perfect and flawless.

22:28.016 --> 22:35.306
And he provided the solution in the person of Jesus Christ.

22:36.047 --> 22:38.450
Acts chapter four, verse 12, tells us,

22:38.786 --> 22:42.631
There is no other name under heaven by which we are saved.

22:43.151 --> 22:48.718
Anyone who gets saved is saved because of what Jesus did on the cross and the resurrection.

22:50.780 --> 22:52.202
That's reality.

22:54.064 --> 22:55.927
Who said, well, what about this group and that group?

22:56.688 --> 22:57.529
That's up to God.

22:58.229 --> 23:06.419
But if someone is saved, it is because of the saving, atoning, death, burial, and resurrection of Jesus.

23:07.581 --> 23:08.722
How that shakes out.

23:08.866 --> 23:11.249
who makes that decision is above our pay grade.

23:12.171 --> 23:14.354
It is Christ and Christ alone.

23:14.614 --> 23:23.627
And as I said, there are eternal ramifications to following Christ, but man, the current temporal ramifications are worth it alone.

23:24.669 --> 23:29.255
It's worth it because of the difference it makes in this life.

23:30.597 --> 23:36.786
Now, Paul continues, verses 14 through 15, and this is,

23:37.122 --> 23:39.725
This is where he gets really, really real with us.

23:41.447 --> 23:46.652
But how can they call on him to save them unless they believe in him?

23:47.393 --> 23:50.697
And how can they believe in him if they have never heard about him?

23:51.257 --> 23:53.920
And how can they hear about him unless someone tells them?

23:54.941 --> 23:58.825
Do you see how absolutely irrefutable the logic is?

24:00.467 --> 24:03.210
And how will anyone go and tell them without being sent?

24:04.111 --> 24:05.493
Acts 1, 8, we've been sent.

24:05.993 --> 24:06.834
We've already been sent.

24:07.618 --> 24:11.063
That is why the scriptures say how beautiful are the feet of messengers.

24:11.544 --> 24:17.032
There it is again messengers who bring good news.

24:18.314 --> 24:25.946
And when you bring good news to someone, it lightens up every part of their lives.

24:26.006 --> 24:31.414
The gospel of Jesus Christ helps everywhere that the light touches.

24:33.978 --> 24:36.402
It's so powerful, even

24:37.506 --> 24:42.372
If you bring good news of Christ to somebody, even your feet are beautiful.

24:44.455 --> 24:45.797
Nobody has beautiful feet.

24:47.079 --> 24:48.561
Remember the last time you went to the beach?

24:51.525 --> 24:54.849
I don't care what they look like from the knees up, their feet are ugly.

24:56.591 --> 24:57.813
Unless you're bringing good news.

24:59.776 --> 25:07.506
When you bring the good news of Christ into someone's life, when you introduce someone to Christ, you bring

25:07.810 --> 25:13.001
beauty and power, grace and truth, freedom and hope.

